      "date": "2013-03-29 17:36:39.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nWe did this a bit for mgs as well, and there I created only dir to dir symlinks and several file symlinks based on that.  Seemed cleaner to me.  You might also restore mntdev while you're at it.  I see now that MGS/fstype is inconsistent with obdfilter so I'll just shut up.\n\n # ls -l /proc/fs/lustre/mgs/MGS/\ntotal 0\n--w------- 1 root root  0 Mar 29 12:30 evict_client\ndr-xr-xr-x 3 root root  0 Mar 29 12:30 exports\n-r--r--r-- 1 root root  0 Mar 29 12:30 filesystems\nlrwxrwxrwx 1 root root 10 Mar 29 12:30 fstype -> osd/fstype\n-r--r--r-- 1 root root  0 Mar 29 12:30 hash_stats\n-rw-r--r-- 1 root root  0 Mar 29 12:30 ir_timeout\ndr-xr-xr-x 2 root root  0 Mar 29 12:30 live\ndr-xr-xr-x 2 root root  0 Mar 29 12:30 mgs\nlrwxrwxrwx 1 root root 10 Mar 29 12:30 mntdev -> osd/mntdev\n-r--r--r-- 1 root root  0 Mar 29 12:30 num_exports\nlrwxrwxrwx 1 root root 32 Mar 29 12:30 osd -> ../../osd-ldiskfs/lustre-MDT0000\n-r-------- 1 root root  0 Mar 29 12:30 srpc_rules\n-r--r--r-- 1 root root  0 Mar 29 12:30 uuid",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
