      "message": "Patch Set 2: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nOh, my bad. I misunderstood that it was looking in the OFD directory each time if the symlink had already been created, not that it was checking the OSD directory if the target exists. \n\nIt definitely makes sense to check if the target exists, or skip creating the dangling symlink.  Sorry for confusion.",
